# Governing documentation

Document authority (highest first): accepted ADR → Domain Specification → schema → workflow → implementation plans.

When editing these paths:

- Do not contradict an accepted ADR without a superseding ADR.
- Permission keys in domains must match or defer to `docs/domains/authorization-permissions.md`.
- No separate display-category hierarchy (ADR-0003).
- Workflows stay record-level (preconditions, records, locks, permissions, failure, idempotency) — not UI mockups.
- Do not add speculative tables/statuses for deferred areas (transfers, RTV, buyback, offline POS, full CRM).
- Cross-domain durable choices → ADR or `docs/implementation/open-decisions.md`, not only a prose tweak.
- Identifier procedures → `docs/reference/identifiers.md` (ADR-0002 remains authoritative for the decision).
